walking---(encoder)------------>Arduino-(plaintext serial port)--->computer
licks-----(capacitive sensor)-->   |                                ^^
                                   |                                ||
                                   |                                ||
                                   |                                ||
                                   |(ttl pulse                      ||
                                   |high when air puff)             ||
                                   |                                ||
                                   |                                ||
                                   |                                ||
                                   |                                ||
                                   |                                ||
                                   V                                ||
                                Microscope-(MES matlab serial port)-||
                                (olympus bxG1WI)                     |
                                                                     |
                                                                     |
                                                                     |
                                                                     |
                                Laser-(Mai Tai 2.X serial port)------|
                                Mait Tai HP



Capacitor switch used:
    https://www.adafruit.com/product/1374

What we want to do:
     set up raspberry pi to replace arduino
     arduino sends a ttl pusle to microscope when it starts recording
     raspberry pi collects and processes video real time using opencv
         MAC = b8:27:eb:2C:7E:5C
             can ip address be viewed through the website?
             sudo raspi-config
                 need to enable camera through settings
                 need to enable ssh through settings
                 need to enable vnc through settings
             pi doesn't require an ethernet cable bc it has wifi
         need to enable ssh on rpi
         ssh -X to see it
             can't do this because everything is displayed ata very low level by the gpu
             instead:
                 on rpi:
                     raspivid -t 0 -l -o tcp://0.0.0.0:3333
                 on computer:
                     vlc tcp/h264://172.26.199.35:3333
             or:
                 pip3 install pyshine cv2
                 and run the code in cameraPreview.py
         raspberry pi model 3b v1.2
         https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/operating-systems/



